Rui Costa to Il Gironale: &quot;Milan? It's a young team, which is currently starting a cycle, and for it's history, Milan deserves to play in Champions League. I understand the fans frustration, but it takes time to become a great team.&quot;<br />
<br />
&quot;Gattuso is a great guy, and he will be a great coach, and I&rsquo;m not saying this only because he was my team mate. Silva? When you arrive at Milan, everybody is expecting a lot, and people have to understand the player and wait for him to get confidence.&quot;

&quot;Currently, we are calm. We have an ownership and a president who deserves more respect from the media, because he always has fulfilled his commitments.&quot;<br />
<br />
&quot;The enthusiasm of the fans? It means a lot. We have always received great enthusiasm from the fans, and this gives us more responsibility to manage Milan.&quot;
